## Database Naming

### Tables

**Plural, snake_case:**
- `users`
- `blog_posts`
- `article_comments`
- `article_tags` (join table)

### Columns

**snake_case:**
- `first_name`
- `email_address`
- `published_at`
- `views_count`
- `is_active` (avoid, use just `active`)

```ruby
# Good
create_table :blog_posts do |t|
  t.string :title
  t.text :body
  t.string :slug
  t.integer :views_count
  t.datetime :published_at
  t.references :user, foreign_key: true
  
  t.timestamps
end

# Bad
create_table :BlogPost do |t|  # Wrong! Use lowercase
  t.string :Title              # Wrong! Use snake_case
  t.text :Body
end
```

### Indexes

**snake_case with descriptive suffix:**
- `index_articles_on_slug`
- `index_articles_on_user_id_and_status`
- `index_users_on_email`

```ruby
# Good
add_index :articles, :slug, unique: true
add_index :articles, [:user_id, :status]

# Rails automatically generates index names, but if custom:
add_index :articles, :slug, name: 'index_articles_on_slug_unique'
```

